    "narrative": "For the May 4th slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (80.08) and **Matt Chapman** (69.87) anchor our offensive effort, benefiting immensely from a soft matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** takes top honors today; his elite projection is bolstered by a favorable wind blowing out and a 13% boost derived from the starter\u2019s xERA of 4.53. Similarly, **Matt Chapman** and **Luis Arraez** (69.53) capitalize on the same environment against V\u00e1squez, with **Luis Arraez** specifically seeing his value climb thanks to a 7% platoon advantage and positive atmospheric conditions. **Cal Raleigh** (63.85) remains a strong play, as he draws a highly exploitable matchup against JR Ritchie, whose 4.60 xERA allows **Cal Raleigh** to maximize his raw power output.\n\nStrategic benching was critical today, with **Jonathan Aranda** (46.44) serving as the primary casualty. While his 0.372 xwOBA is respectable, he suffered a 12% penalty due to the unfavorable platoon split against Lauer, leaving him just outside the threshold for active duty compared to our higher-upside starters. We are monitoring **Tyler Freeman** (60.18) closely; despite his favorable park adjustment, he carries a 34% rain risk that could compromise his efficiency if the game is shortened. Meanwhile, **Will Smith** (48.90) and **Taylor Ward** (47.31) present the most marginal starting profiles. **Taylor Ward** faces the toughest challenge of the group against the 3.45 xERA of Schlittler, though his top-of-the-order positioning provides just enough volume to justify the start over bench options like **Yainer Diaz** (45.24), who faces the elite arm of Yoshinobu Yamamoto. Proceed with caution on **Tyler Freeman** as the weather reports evolve.",
